				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Rizlona's Fire vs other options<a name="34620"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 14 04 11:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Strum,
<br />
   I saved and saved and saved, tortured my friends by making them do MM missions with me until I got the points for Rizlona's. My personal results? A good solid noticable increase in nuke damage, but it barely ever gets a spell slot because I just don't have room. My standard song lists are dependent on what classes are in the group as always, so I'm constantly shifting them around to fill in the gaps. There is rarely a need for the increase because I personally play with a lot of tanks and melee, I do throw it in on raids when I end up in a group with a bunch of nukers, but they are usually 60+ so it doesn't help much. My personal advice to you would be to save up for the Dire Melodies aug, but remember that it's a type 4 (I think) so you need LDoN armor to use it. I would reccommend saving for the EF armor, only the BP has the slot type you need. I'm currently saving for the BP, I have almost 400 EF points and each piece is around 650 (if I remember). The Dire Melodies aug is around 250 MM points, that didn't take long. 
<br />
    Depending on your own personal play style, you may or may not find Rizlona's useful. I still pull it out every once in awhile but now that I'm almost 58 I keep ending up in PoV or high risk LDoN groups with higher level friends, so the song doesn't always apply. It's really your call but I hope this helps. 
<br />
   On a side note, do EF as much as you can, not only for the armor, but because Call of the Muse is much much better than Rizlona's and you're going to want the points for it when you hit 65. 
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps
<br />
 <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
