				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Rizlona's Fire vs other options<a name="42934"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 28 04 12:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The Wind Augment is Type 3.  It is WONDERFUL to have, if you don't have your Epic yet.
<br />

<br />
Here is the trouble:  getting an item with a type 3 slot.
<br />

<br />
Aggressor's BP in EC camp is the cheapest item with a type 3 slot to get, but it's not a great BP.  I used it for a long time just because of the aug.  Death Embracer's in MM is better, and should last you into your 50s, when you have some hope of getting your epic, and/or raiding for a better BP etc.
<br />

<br />
There is a 200ish point earring at the Everfrost camp that has a type 3 slot.  It's a pretty ho-hum earring, but it is worth having a relatively crappy earring to have a 1.4 boost on MR debuff on mez and charm, and to not have to bother with your flute to invis.
<br />

<br />
I skipped the Rizlona's song, and did ok.  I often got groups where I was Puller / CC / Haster / Slower, so there would not have been room for it.  If you get a lot of groups with shammies and chanters, then it might be worth having (you might have a spot for it).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
